quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  43,74,"Indeed the criminals will stay in the punishment of hell forever."
  43,75,"And it will never be lightened upon them, and they will remain in it devastated."
  43,76,"And We did not oppress them at all, but they themselves were unjust."
  43,77,"And they will cry out, “O Malik*, ask your Lord to finish us!” He will answer, “Rather you are to stay (forever).” (*The guard of hell)"
  43,78,"Indeed We have brought the Truth to you, but most of you detest the Truth."
  43,79,"Do they assume that they have made their work thorough? So We shall make Our work thorough."
  43,80,"Do they fancy that We do not listen to their whispers and their counselling? Why not, We surely do! And Our angels are with them, writing down."
  43,81,"Proclaim (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him), “If supposedly, the Most Gracious had an offspring* – I would be the first to worship!” (*Which is impossible)"
  43,82,"Purity is to the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne, from all what they fabricate."
  43,83,"Therefore leave them to utter vile speech and to play, until they confront the day which they are promised."
  43,84,"And only He is the God of the heavenly creation and the God of the earthly creation; and He only is the Wise, the All Knowing."
  43,85,"And Most Auspicious is He, for Whom is the kingship of the heavens and the earth and all that is between them; and only with Him is the knowledge of the Last Day; and towards Him you are to return."
  43,86,"And those whom they worship besides Allah do not have the right of intercession – the right of intercession is only for those who testify to the Truth and have knowledge."
  43,87,"And if you ask them as to Who created them, they will surely answer “Allah” – so where are they reverting?"
  43,88,"And by oath of the saying of My Prophet “O my Lord! These people do not accept faith!”"
  43,89,"Therefore excuse them and proclaim, “Peace”; for they will soon come to know."
